	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I can think of 4 possible sources of distortion:
<br /><ul><li> parasitic inductance and capacitance of either of these kinds of resistors is such that you really shouldn't be able to hear any distortion from the substrate material at all</li><li> Since neither material is a semiconductor, I don't think you would encounter burst noise</li><li> The resistance is too small for shot noise, and </li><li> neither is foam-like so flicker noise seems unlikely too.</li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


